        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were a scout in WW2, one of the lucky ones, since you lived to the end of the war, and returned home.  You found yourself incredibly disconnected from the non-combatants around you, and couldn't find a job anyway.  You started using your skills from the war to hunt for meat and furs so that you could still provide for your family.  Your sire watched you for weeks before he struck, and then he watched you work out how to survive for a month before he revealed himself to you.  After the horrors of war, it was easier to accept that there were monsters in the shadows. It was comforting to realize that the war wasn't entirely the work of humanity, and you were more than open to the idea of fighting the monsters who had created this Jyhad.  Before the week of nightmares, you were plagued by visions. Those ended when the world, well, didn't, but the rest of your pack didn't make it through correctly.  Your sire survived, but the toll of the events was such that he chose to walk into the flames of a Fire Dance rather than jump.  You and Verka were the ones who thought of forming Bundle.  (One alone was easily broken, but together you could all be strong.)  You don't miss Verka all that much, but you aren't sure if Bright is the best choice for Ductus.  You're exerting your authority more as you find yourself disagreeing with them, but you do agree that San Diego is a good place for your pack."
        ],
